RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 27700. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHAIRMAN LAYLA was nudged on early to get inside position leading into the first turn, dictated terms down the backside, was well rated getting a breather bunching up the field at the three furlong marker, spurted clear when roused in upper stretch and held safe comfortably crossing the line. TWIXTER travelled in midfield two wide on the first turn, stalked near the rear outside foes down the backstretch, advanced between rivals when scrubbed on splitting foes three wide at the quarter marker and chased the winner down the stretch besting the rest at the wire. SPANISH SERENADE was unhurried trailing in the early stages, began to pick up runners four wide around horses at the quarter pole and finished with intent outside foes through the stretch to be a clear third in the end. KINZHAL settled on the rail in midpack in the early going, rated kindly nestled on the fence down the backside, had clear run inside with five sixteenths to go and made little impact on the fence down the lane for a minor share. MANETKA pressed between foes on the first turn, hounded the pacesetting winner down the backside, was urged midpoint on the far turn chasing the leader but to no avail and faltered between rivals in the three path at the furlong pole. LITTLE DOMI prompted the pace three wide into the first turn, continued to keep a close eye on the frontrunning winner three deep down the backstretch, came under a ride trying to match strides with the leaders midway on the final turn, made no headway and retreated in upper stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 2 5F Inner turf CR: 75. Claiming Purse 40200. INNER TURF FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Le ss Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMART COVERAGE chased the pacesetter two deep at the half, battled for the front outside on the turn, cleared off for the lead at the quarter pole and held on at the finish by a diminishing margin when crossing the wire. JMR SPEEDY ESCAPE tracked the contesting pair on the rail at the half, waited inside on the turn, was roused on the rail turning for home and rallied up the fence late to better two rivals for place at the finish. VERY DEBONAIRE took command in the beginning, dueled for the lead running inside through the turn, could not keep pace with the winner quickening at the quarter pole and stubbornly gave way in deep stretch between horses to lose the runners up share in the end. SEA TO AIR rated in midpack outside foes down the backstretch, rallied two wide outside runners three furlongs from the wire, was in range three wide straightening out for the drive and ran on determinedly outside down the stretch but was on the wrong end of the three way finish for place at the wire. SILENT RISK stalked on the rail near the rear, could see the field saving ground running on the turn and showed some interest passing weary foes down the lane. MIDNIGHT MOONSHINE travelled in the middle of the field on the rail down the backside, was roused through the turn but could not get involved and had little to show driving to the finish line. BEE BEE THE KING had a slow start trailing in the beginning inside, put in a mild run two wide outside foes from the three eighths marker to the quarter pole and emptied out turning for home.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 3 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 81. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 111000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $9,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR RESTRICTED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $75,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Claiming Since July 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Cl aiming Price $75,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UPHILL DANCE settled alone in midpack under a tight rein down the backside, cruised around foes midway on the turn, was urged three wide at the quarter pole, quickly pouncing on horses to take command at the furlong marker and drew away convincingly in deep stretch. TWO GHOSTS bobbled slightly on the break, regrouped to track the frontrunner three deep down the backstretch, was ridden for more going after the leader at the quarter pole to be in the hunt three wide between rivals for the drive, was no match for the closing winner at the furlong marker and stubbornly held off the stablemate for the runners up share at the wire. PONTIAC was void of speed trailing in the early going inside, improved on the rail at the half under a hold, was checked mildly in tight quarters shuffled back some with three eighths remaining and found his best stride late closing in to just miss getting up for place at the finish. CRAFTY OAKS tracked the frontrunner in the two path in the beginning, was hard ridden on the rail midpoint on the turn keeping pace with the leaders, had a chance for a share on the fence at the top of the lane and finished up one paced to the wire for a minor role in the end. NATURAL STAR stalked three deep near the rear down the back straight, could not keep up with others running through the turn and showed some interest late catching up to pass the early pacesetter that was tiring at the finish. CLASSY IMAGE cleared from the outside post to set the pace on the rail down the backside, comfortably dictated terms through the turn, was collared outside turning for home, offered little resistance in upper stretch and faltered with a sixteenth from the finish.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 5 7F All Weather Track CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 27700. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MENTORING hopped at the break, pressed on the rail in the beginning, had a narrow lead inside at the half mile marker, opened up while in hand running on the turn to have a comfortable lead straightening out for the drive and was kept to the task late for an impressive win. PREETZAH'S STAR travelled three deep in midfield down the backside, circled four wide making a sharp move outside rivals through the turn, chased the winner but to no avail down the stretch and held for second in a solid effort besting the rest. WONT FORGET YOU stalked near the rear down the backstretch, was on hold trailing on the fence behind a runner with three furlongs to go, was steadied a couple of times losing momentum on the rail through the turn, rallied between horses in the two path at the quarter pole and was full of run late closing with each stride down the lane to be a hard luck third at the finish. HARPER CITY trailed in the early going, began to extend ones stride three wide commencing at the three eighths pole going around horses, was in the mix for a piece of the prize four wide turning for home but levelled out at the furlong marker to be on the fringes at the end. NO MORE SALT had a good spot watching the engaging pair at the half, could not maintain forward position when roused three furlongs from home and faded with a quarter mile left to run. BROTHER BELEN had a slim advantage outside leaving the chute, was relegated to a chasing role at the half, could not keep up to the winner who was opening up on rivals with three furlongs from the finish and backed through the field on the rail at the quarter pole. SING DIXIE broke in at the start, travelled in the middle of the pack with runners on either side down the backstretch, could not reach contention running two wide throughout the turn and was never a presence driving to the wire. COMMANDER AT SEA settled in mid-pack on the rail down the back straight, was coaxed for more on the fence through the turn, offered little response and backed away with two furlongs to run and had nothing to give in the stretch run.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 7 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 69. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 49600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD ONTARIO SIRED MAIDENS THAT HAVE RACED 3 CONSECUTIVE STARTS IN THE MAIDEN OPTIONAL $40,000 / OS CATEGORY IN 2022-23 AND DID NOT FINISH 2ND THRU 4TH. or FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $23,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DREAMS AND SCHEMES settled in the middle of the field two wide in the beginning stages, improved smartly on the fence down the backstretch, began to reel in the loose pacesetter with three eighths to go, collared the early leader outside under a vigorous hand ride in upper stretch and held safe when roused for more in the final furlong. I'M SNOW ANGEL broke out at the start, was allowed to settle co-trailing inside on the first turn, could see the field three deep outside rivals down the backside, made a sharp move swooping around horses three furlongs to the wire, posed the only threat to the winner at the top of the lane and stubbornly chased in deep stretch but could not get there in the end. BRIEF co-trailed stalking three wide in the first turn, settled on the rail near the rear down the backside, had to be throttled down, on hold, stuck behind a tiring rival with five sixteenths from home, shifted outside splitting foes two wide at the quarter pole starting a run and finished with intent to close in late to capture third nearing the wire. CENTENARY was hustled for the lead into the first turn, became headstrong loose up front entering the backstretch to open up on the field at the half, began to weaken clinging to a diminishing lead midpoint on the final turn, was collared by the winner in upper stretch and tired on the fence in the last sixteenth. TAKE CHANCES tracked two wide in the early stages, could not get interested losing ground to others down the backstretch, was asked for run three furlongs from the wire and lacked a finish in the stretch run. BAREFOOT SERVANTU was bumped inside on the break, tracked on the rail in the first turn, chased the lone pace down the back straight, retreated midway on the far turn and could not be a factor running to the wire.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 32800. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $9,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ECHO WITH LAUGHTER tracked three deep on the outside in the early going, took closer order to hound the pace outside three furlongs from home, gained control at the quarter pole opening up by the time he entered the top of stretch and safely cruised home for the victory. GRAND AMBITION travelled inside in the third flight with four furlongs from the finish, made no headway between runners losing positions midway through the turn, shifted outside in the five path stubbornly fighting on at the top of the lane, found his best stride late and closed determinedly to be a clear second at the finish. DISCOVERY CHART trailed the field inside down the back straightaway, could still see the field while looking for a seam at the quarter pole, was blocked behind runners at the top of the lane, weaved through horses at the furlong pole and surged late bursting up the rail near the wire to capture third. IT'S ME MARIO was improving four deep around horses at the half, continued a good sustained run circling three wide at the quarter pole to be in range of the leader five wide for the stretch drive, chased the winner in upper stretch, wilted while on the wrong lead in the final sixteenth and was just edged out late for the third money. MR. DE was bumped soundly on the break, settled three deep between foes near the rear down the backside, was scrubbed on gaining mildly three wide outside horses through the turn, was in with a chance for a small share six wide for the stretch drive but stalled and levelled off in the final sixteenth. SMOKIN HOLIDAY settled close to the back of the pack two deep between rivals at the half, was shuffled back to last three furlongs from the wire, angled outside commencing a run at the quarter pole around foes, swung out widest in the seven path for the drive and ran on willingly to the finish. AMAZON FORESTER stalked on the rail close to the rear in the early stages, made little impact running on the fence throughout the turn, had a clear path inside turning for home and finished up mildly to the wire. PALACE RING broke out slightly on the start, tracked the pacesetter on the rail down the backside, watched the contesting duo with three eights to go, came under a ride going in the wrong direction at the quarter pole, had little to give in the stretch run, was pulled up galloping out and vanned back to the barn. BELLASPINA settled in mid-pack third flight three deep outside at the half, made a brief run through the turn to be in the mix between runners for a minor role two furlongs from the prize but came up empty in the four path for the drive and flattened out at the furlong marker. ONLY LOVE was loose on the lead down the backstretch, maintained a narrow advantage on the winner inside three furlongs from the wire, was collared at the quarter pole and stopped on the fence in mid-stretch.
